%0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", stats1.errors_out, stats1.errortime_out);\n251: \telse $display("Hint: Output \'out\' has no mismatches.");\n252: \n253: \t$display("Hint: Total mismatched samples is %1d out of %1d samples\\n", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n254: \t$display("Simulation finished at %0d ps", $time);\n255: \t$display("Mismatches: %1d in %1d samples", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n256: \tend\n257: \tendmodule\n\n</previous_tb>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "The user requires two main deliverables: an IO interface matching the golden testbench\'s usage, and an improved golden testbench. \\n\\n**1. Interface Generation:** I must adhere strictly to the ports used in the `golden_testbench`\'s instantiation of `stimulus_gen`, `RefModule`, and `TopModule`. The interface must declare all ports as `logic`.\\n\\n**2. Testbench Improvement:** The golden testbench needs modification to satisfy specific output requirements:\\n    *   Maintain exact functionality, interface, and module instantiation from the previous successful version (which was used as the base for the previous attempts).\\n    *   Maintain the original error counting logic (stats1.errors and stats1.errors_out).\\n    *   Crucially, upon simulation end, display exactly: \\"SIMULATION PASSED\\" if no mismatch occurs, or \\"SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y\\" otherwise.\\n    *   If the first mismatch occurs, display inputs, actual output, and expected output at that time.\\n    *   For multi-bit signals, display HEX and BINARY format if width <= 64.\\n\\n**Syntax Error Analysis & Corrections (based on failed logs):**\\n*   **Port Declarations in Instantiations:** The failed logs pointed to syntax errors in instance port expressions (e.g., lines 163, 161, 175, 177). In the previous TB, `stimulus_gen` ports were inconsistently declared